            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
            Reverend Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>At the suggestion of Mr. Ezekiel<lb/> of Cincinnati&#44; I take the liberty of giving you my<lb/> proxy as a delegate to the Council of American<lb/> Hebrew Congregations.  Professional engagements prevent my<lb/> going.  I represent one of the few orthodox Congre&#45;<lb/>gations that belong to the Union &#38; do not know of<lb/> any better proxy than yourself to take my place.<lb/></p>
            <p>There is a measure I would advocate&#44; if I was on<lb/> the spot&#44; &#38; in which you will agree with me&#44; no doubt.<lb/>  We made three years ago at Cleveland&#44; and arrangement<lb/> with Dr. DeSola&#44; for 1000 Bibles of Leeser&#39;s version<lb/> which the &#34;Union&#34; sold at &#36;1 a piece.  These are all<lb/> sold&#44; &#38; we ought to take another thousand&#44; and again<lb/> sell them for not more than &#36;1 a piece.<lb/></p>
            <p>Please ask Mr. Bettman to show you my report<lb/> as visitor of the college&#44; &#38; see to its being laid before<lb/> the council&#44; if the report of the other visitors is laid<lb/> before it.<lb/></p>
            <p>Respectfully<lb/>
            Lewis N Dembitz<lb/>
                Louisville Ky July 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1877.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Revd. S. Morais<lb/>
                &#40;Portug. Synag.&#41;<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa<lb/></p>
        </body>
